`StringBuilder` is &quot;generally&quot; a better solution if you want to do `String` concatenation in Java, but this might be some what of a over kill for this example.

So, taking an input like `Elmar DidOkLTWdeee 123456` the above methods will output `eLMAR dIDoKltwDEEE 123456`

Elaborating @Dawood ibn Kareem&#39;s comment, you don&#39;t need the nested loop a simple `if-else` would do it.

	if(Character.isLetter(c)){
